The Flintstones & WWE: Stone Age SmackDown is a direct-to-video film starring The Flintstones. It is the second co-production between Warner Bros. Animation and WWE Studios following Scooby-Doo! WrestleMania Mystery. The film features Fred Flintstone, Barney Rubble and the whole Bedrock gang with stone age versions of WWE Superstars and Divas.  It is the first new Flintstones production in over fourteen years since On the Rocks, fifty-five years after the original 1960s series and also the first Flintstones film without original creators, Bill Hanna and Joe Barbera who have died respectively a decade ago (the 2000s).
